==English==
===Nominal phrase===
'''[[home]] [[run]]''' (plural: [[home runs]])

#{{baseball}} A four-base [[hit]], a [[homer]]
#: ''The first baseman hit a '''home run''' to lead off the ninth.''
#{{idiom}} The portion of a journey that ends at home
#: ''I'm on the '''home run'''.
#{{idiom}} A [[success]]; especially, a popular success.
#:''The product was a '''home run'''.''


